The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strlen(value) can read beyond the bounds of the object pointed to by value if value is NULL or not terminated by a NUL character. For example, if the caller passes a non-NUL-terminated buffer or NULL, strlen(value) will scan out-of-bounds (or dereference NULL), violating Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

